name: Jennifer Manzella
text: My daughter attended Bay City for about a year and a half.  This place is a gymnastics mill.  The instructors change constantly so they never recognize your child's skills.  So, she was "learning" the same thing her last day there that she was her first - a year and a half later!  She didn't progress, she just kept doing the same stuff she was bored with week after week.  It got to the point where she didn't want to go - and this is a child who LOVES gymnastics.  Final straw was when she learned to do her back walkover at home and showed her teachers at the next class.  I asked what they said, and her answer was, "they didn't care."  We finally transferred to another school and the difference is amazing.  She's back to being happy when we pick her up for gymnastics and is learning so much more.

text: I love EGC!! Please do not pay attention to the person below. Mr. Jeff is one of the nicest coaches I ever had! I competed for this gym for 4 years and it was the best experience of my life! Since it has been said that he dose like military that must be a joke since Mr.Jeff  is a veteran and two of his children are in the military! As of now they are not able to have boys gymnastic since the demand and resources are not available but they are able to sign up for tumbling and cheer classes.  This is a wonderful place for gymnast of any age!

name: Mandy Abernathy
text: I am very disheartened to read of the first review.  Enterprise Gymnastics and Cheer isn't just a gym but a family to me.  Jeff Pangallo has been nothing but professional to all three of my daughters that attended, my oldest also being on the competitive team Level 4 then 5.  He truly cares about the girls in a "non-creepily" way and has devoted so much of his life to gymnastics.  It angers me to read such a harsh review of this gym!  Every single staff member has been nothing but courteous and professional to not only my children but myself as well.  We are a military family and it broke our hearts to leave Enterprise and the gym!  We have yet to find a gym that begins to compare to EGC.  I highly recommend this gym and Mr Jeff to everyone whether you have children just starting out to girls on a more advanced level.  I cannot say enough how much this gym means to us, DO NOT hesitate to sign your kids up.  Call and schedule a trial class!

name: Heather Mitchell
text: I have two children enrolled at EGC.  We have been enrolled and taking classes at this gym for 6 years and have been very pleased.  Mr. Jeff and his staff work very hard to push each student to do their best.  I have had girls in the regular progressive classes, the cheernastics class as well as on the competitive gymnastics team and have encountered nothing but professionalism from the coaches.  I have never witnessed inappropriate behavior among any of EGC's staff.  My children have learned gymnastics and cheer skills while having fun and they have enjoyed every aspect of the classes as well as the team practices.  I know it has been asked about boys being enrolled in the gymnastics classes and the answer seems apparent as boy's gymnastics requires different equipment.  This is equipment that EGC does not have nor do they have room for it.  Boys are however allowed to participate in the cheernastics classes.  I intend to be a part of the EGC family for years to come as I also have an infant and I am already making plans to enroll her as soon as she is walking.  If you are looking for a gym in the Enterprise area, then I highly recommend EGC.

name: Michael Jones
text: I LOVE being a part of the Head Over Heels family!  And I say that because it does indeed feel like family here.  The two owners are very personable and outstanding at what they do, and they expect the same out of all the staff.  My daughter has been taking gymnastics here since she was 4, and she is now 7, in her first year of competitive gymnastics.  I had no idea what to expect, both financially and procedurally, and the gym has a wonderful parent organization that explains all you need to know going into competition.  There are ample opportunities for fundraisers to offset your monthly costs, and the teams really bond with each other - both the kids (girls have teams and boys have teams as well) and the parents.  We drive about 15 miles to get here, when two other local gyms are closer, because Head Over Heels is THAT good.  We are VERY pleased, and our daughter LOVES it too!

name: Melissa Sievering
text:
I moved my daughter to Nasser at the beginning of 2020! She has excelled at Nasser! They are structured and goal driven! They do new things each week while practicing repetition! For example, they do a
Series of handstands back and forth on the big floor. My 5 year old is really impressive with her handstands and knows the terminology they use as well! They are being trained to learn proper stance and hand etiquette when coming out of handstands and cartwheels! They also learn how to touch and get onto the balance beams. The emphasis on learning these key basics and it is very impressive to me! I was not a gymnast growing up, so seeing these things beinging drilled into our girls makes me feel like i am getting my monies worth and also giving her the best chance to be the best gymnast she can be! Especially since my girl is 5! There is a goal in mind for each gymnast and you can tell that is their main focus each week for every one of the gymnast! There isn’t any mass chaos! We love it here and cannot wait to see what the future holds for our girl!

resp.text: Thank you so VERY much Melissa for your kind words and the wonderful review! We truly pride ourselves in our coaches' abilities to make their classes informative and fun all at the same time! We love nothing more than watching these little ones grow into incredible gymnasts, and it all starts from learning the basic skills throughout their classes! We appreciate you for being able to see that the smallest details in technique matters. Love, your Navy Nation!!
